<HEADLINE>
<P>
A GUIDE TO GALAVANTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By L.M. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
How to get there: Although most major airlines fly to New Orleans, Southwest 
Airlines is offering an economical fare of $218 round trip, with only a one-day 
advance purchase necessary. This is the same low fare usually offered as a 
22-day advance purchase. 
</P>
<P>
Call Southwest at (213) 485-1221. 
</P>
<P>
Halloween tours and events: Friends of the Cabildo's "Ghostly Galavant Through 
the French Quarter" takes place next Sunday from 1:30 to 4:30 p.m. Price: $25 
per person or $22.50 per person for groups of 10 or more. Contact The Friends 
of the Cabildo for reservations: (504) 523-3939. 
</P>
<P>
"Save Our Cemeteries" offers one-hour tours of atmospheric Lafayette Cemetery 
on Mondays, Wednesdays and Fridays at 10:30 a.m. Meeting spot is Washington 
Gate in the 1400 block of Washington Avenue. Cost $5 per person. 
</P>
<P>
"The Haunted Dungeon of Musee Conti" is a well-known wax museum filled with 
spooky Louisiana legends. Along with local horrors such as Marie Laveau's 
voodoo slaves, the casket girls and Napoleon himself, the museum has added the 
likes of Dracula, Frankenstein and the Hunchback of Notre Dame for Halloween 
chills. Call (504) 525-2605. Musee Conti is at 917 Conti St., and is open from 
10 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
For more information on Halloween festivities in the city, call the New Orleans 
Tourist Board at (504) 566-5068. L.M. 
</P>
