<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHLAND ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
SAN LUIS OBISPO TAKES TO AIR FOR 29-0 WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
David Lafferty led the Cal Poly-San Luis Obispo offense by passing for two 
touchdowns and 231 yards, and the Poly defense held Santa Clara to 99 net yards 
Saturday in a 29-0 Western Football Conference victory over the Broncos in 
Santa Clara. 
</P>
<P>
Cal Poly, 6-1 overall and 2-1 in WFC play, also got three field goals from Tom 
McCook. 
</P>
<P>
The touchdown passes were caught by Vince Holloway and Aaron Brubaker. Baldomar 
Cortez ran for a late touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Clara (5-3, 1-2) had 37 net yards rushing, with six quarterback sacks 
biting into the total. 
</P>
<P>
Aron Wise, averaging 138 yards rushing before Saturday, was held to 51 net 
yards. 
</P>
<P>
Azusa Pacific 27, Menlo 0 -- Quarterback Brian Hunt completed 27 of 55 passes 
for 338 yards and connected with Dan Jensen on touchdown pass plays of 34 and 
five yards as the Cougars (5-1) beat Menlo (5-2) in a nonconference game at 
Azusa. 
</P>
<P>
Hayward St. 19, San Francisco St. 13 -- Running back Tony Randall rushed for 
162 yards in 28 carries and scored one touchdown as Hayward State snapped a 
six-game losing streak with a 19-13 victory over San Francisco State in 
Hayward. 
</P>
<P>
Hayward's Jesse Tautalatasi, who rushed for 84 yards in 21 carries, scored the 
deciding touchdown from one yard with 2 minutes 45 seconds remaining in the 
third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Randall scored on a one-yard run with 5:13 remaining in the first quarter of 
the Northern California Athletic Conference game to tie the contest at 7-7. 
</P>
<P>
Hayward St. improved to 2-6 overall and 1-1 in conference play. San Francisco 
St. fell to 2-5 overall and 0-2 in conference. 
</P>
