<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rancho Santiago 43, Orange Coast 15 -- Estrus Crayton, playing a little more 
than one half, ran for 121 yards and four touchdowns to lead the Dons at Orange 
Coast College. 
</P>
<P>
Crayton, a sophomore tailback, surpassed the 2,000-yard mark in his career when 
he scored on an 11-yard run in the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
He also scored on runs of 15, 22 and three yards. Crayton has 724 yards this 
season, and 2,064 yards in his career. 
</P>
<P>
Crayton's four touchdowns raised his conference-leading total to 17. He had 20 
last season and has scored 230 points in his 16-game career. 
</P>
<P>
"It was a very typical night for him," Rancho Santiago Coach Dave Ogas said. 
"He's just an amazing kid." 
</P>
<P>
Orange Coast (4-2, 2-2) did its part to make things even easier for Rancho 
Santiago (4-2, 2-2) by turning the ball over eight times. The first five were 
fumbles and the next three interceptions. 
</P>
<P>
Dave Spoolstra had an interception and recovered a fumble, Justin Mills, 
Richard Valenzuela, and Scott Strini recovered fumbles and Gary Bladow and 
Scott McMahon got interceptions. STEVE KRESAL 
