<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEWAGE SPILL CAUSES QUARANTINE OF SHORE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
County Health Department workers posted quarantine signs along a stretch of bay 
shoreline in the 5100 block of North Harbor Drive Saturday morning because of a 
sewage spill. 
</P>
<P>
The quarantine occurred after a grease blockage in the 1500 block of Rosecrans 
Boulevard caused about 1,200 gallons of raw sewage to spill into the bay. 
</P>
<P>
Christina Graulau, county health department spokeswoman, said that the spill 
was stopped about 11 a.m. Saturday, but the shoreline quarantine will remain in 
effect for at least 24 hours. 
</P>
