<HEADLINE>
<P>
YAMAGUCHI LANDS SEVEN TRIPLES AND BEATS ITO AT SKATE AMERICA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BUFFALO, N.Y. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kristi Yamaguchi of Fremont, Calif., scored her second major upset in two 
months, beating 1989 world champion Midori Ito of Japan at the Skate America 
competition. 
</P>
<P>
Yamaguchi, who beat reigning world champion Jill Trenary at the Goodwill Games, 
landed seven triple jumps in her four-minute performance. 
</P>
<P>
Ito started strong with a soaring triple lutz before failing on her trademark 
triple Axel jump, touching the ice with both hands to keep from falling. 
</P>
<P>
Stefania Calegari and Pasquale Camerlengo of Italy easily won the ice dancing 
event. They won all three phases of the event with their innovative free dance 
set to a circus theme. The French team of Isabelle Sarech and Zavier Debernis 
finished second. The top Americans were Jeanne Miley and Michael Verlich, who 
finished sixth. 
</P>
