<HEADLINE>
<P>
PACIFIC'S KOPP PASSES FOR 564 YARDS AND 5 TOUCHDOWNS IN 62-24 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
STOCKTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Quarterback Troy Kopp passed for 564 yards and receiver Aaron Turner had 11 
catches for 265 yards in leading Pacific to a 62-24 Big West Conference victory 
over New Mexico State Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
Kopp, a sophomore from Mission Viejo High, completed 28 of 46 passes, with five 
going for touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
He also ran for 37 yards and a touchdown. He broke the school record of 515 
passing yards he had set last Saturday against Cal State Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
The NCAA record for passing yardage, and total yardage, in a game is 631, set 
by Utah's Scott Mitchell against Air Force in 1988. 
</P>
<P>
Turner broke the school record of 182 yards receiving by Gary Woznick against 
New Mexico State in 1965. 
</P>
<P>
Pacific is 3-4 overall, 2-3 in the Big West. New Mexico State is 0-7, 0-4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story; Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
