<P>
SETBACK FOR CONDO PROJECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A nine-unit condominium project in the planning stages for more than three 
years received another setback Wednesday when the City Council rejected the 
developers' request to build a higher-than-permitted front wall. 
</P>
<P>
Developers of the proposed complex at 167-175 Monterey Road now must wait at 
least a year before submitting revamped plans. 
</P>
<P>
During a public hearing, residents living near the 46,500-square-foot site 
complained that the design of the proposed complex is incompatible with the 
neighborhood. They also argued that the complex would disrupt the hillside 
ecology. 
</P>
<P>
The vote was 4 to 1, with Councilman James Woollacott Jr. dissenting. 
</P>
