<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: TRUCK CRASHES INTO CAR, TRAPPING YOUTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KIRSTEN LEE SWARTZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Thousand Oaks teen-ager was trapped in his car for more than an hour Saturday 
afternoon and a second teen-ager was injured when one of the boys swerved into 
oncoming traffic to avoid hitting a car that had stopped in front of him, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The Ventura County Fire Department worked with the Jaws of Life to free David 
Stufkosky from his car, closing Avenida de Los Arboles, one of the city's major 
streets, for more than two hours. 
</P>
<P>
Stufkosky, 18, was at Los Robles Regional Medical Center last night with an 
open fracture to his left leg and head injuries, said Sgt. Will Howe of the 
Ventura County Sheriff's Department. 
</P>
<P>
Troy Waters, 16, suffered moderate injuries, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Waters, traveling east in a pickup truck about 3 p.m., swerved head-on into 
Stufkosky's car after the car in front of Waters stopped to make a left turn. 
The impact pushed the front of Stufkosky's sedan onto his body. KIRSTEN LEE 
SWARTZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
