<P>
Photo, COLOR, TRAVELING IN STYLE: PARTING SHOT: Sometimes, escape can mean no 
more than putting your feet up, reading a novel or catching a few winks. And 
should you fail to react when a passing stranger alights on your toe for a 
moment or two, it means you've learned how to really unwind. JIM MENDENHALL 
</P>
