<HEADLINE>
<P>
PLEASE DON'T TESTIFY, TOBY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I really don't mind that Roy Schaeffer's cat, Toby, has an appraiser's 
certificate ("Appraiser Certificate Really the Cat's Meow" by H. W. Moss Oct. 
14). 
</P>
<P>
I'm sort of a live-and-let-live guy, and if Toby needs a hobby, appraising real 
estate seems harmless enough. It's just that I don't want Toby to be testifying 
as an expert witness in eminent domain valuation cases, which -- judging from 
the reported court decisions -- he seems to be doing with regularity. 
</P>
<P>
GIDEON KANNER 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
<P>
 Kanner is Editor and Publisher of a monthly periodical on eminent domain. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
