<HEADLINE>
<P>
RERUNS TO RE-WATCH; 
</P>
<P>
CAROL BURNETT, U.S.M.C. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOAN FANTAZIA, Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
If the Marines sent Pvt. Gomer Pyle to Saudi Arabia, we wouldn't have to worry 
about war in the Middle East. Gomer would either melt Saddam Hussein's hardened 
heart or send him right into a straitjacket. 
</P>
<P>
Gomer (Jim Nabors) tries his best, but go-o-olly, does he drive Sgt. Carter 
crazy. This time, however, Gomer's the one who could be driven crazy-by Cpl. 
Carol. 
</P>
<P>
Carol Burnett, as a love-starved Marine on Gomer Pyle, U.S.M.C. (Friday at 2:30 
a.m. on TBS), falls hard for Gomer, who keeps dating her because she never 
gives him a chance to tell her he's already got a girlfriend-Lou-Ann Poovie 
(Elizabeth MacRae). Burnett is at her infuriating and pathetic best. 
</P>
<P>
"Corporal Carol" originally aired in September, 1967, a couple weeks after her 
own series, "The Carol Burnett Show," made its debut. Nabors would sometimes 
turn up on Burnett's comedy series, too. 
</P>
<P>
Gomer, whose show was a spinoff of "The Andy Griffith Show," never forgot his 
Mayberry roots and was occasionally visited by old pals Andy, Goober, Opie and, 
this week, Aunt Bee (Thursday at 2:30 a.m. on TBS). 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Carol Burnett and Jim Nabors, right, visited each others' shows in the 
late '60s. An early morning episode Friday of "Gomer Pyle, U.S.M.C." has Cpl. 
Carol falling for Gomer in a big way. On TBS. 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
